ral moment at the turn of the twentieth century-when the frontier ended, the United States entered the modern era, and homosexuality was created as a category-Boag shows how the American people, and thus the American nation, were bequeathed an unambiguous heterosexual identity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aCross-dresserszWest (U.S.)xHistoryy19th century. 0aGender identityxHistoryx19th centuryxWest (U.S.). 0aGender identityzWest (U.S.)xHistoryy19th century. 0aHomosexualityxHistoryx19th centuryxWest (U.S.). 0aHomosexualityzWest (U.S.)xHistoryy19th century. 0aTransvestitesxHistoryx19th centuryxWest (U.S.). 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520949959423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520949959.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles